To find (A x B) U (A x {z}), we first need to find the Cartesian products A x B and A x {z}.

A x B = {(1, x), (1, y), (2, x), (2, y), (3, x), (3, y)}

A x {z} = {(1, z), (2, z), (3, z)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:

(A x B) U (A x {z}) = {(1, x), (1, y), (2, x), (2, y), (3, x), (3, y), (1, z), (2, z), (3, z)}
